{"error":0,"message":null,"data":{"name":"HT Mega Addons for Elementor &#8211; Elementor Widgets &amp; Template Builder","plugin":"ht-mega-for-elementor","link":"https:\/\/wordpress.org\/plugins\/ht-mega-for-elementor\/","latest":"1782273120","closed":0,"vulnerability":[{"uuid":"ee8d9e4d354c1bab9c9378873348c013358c4090a85b45705b3843c232660f01","name":"HT Mega Addons for Elementor &#8211; Elementor Widgets &amp; Template Builder [ht-mega-for-elementor] < 1.5.7","description":null,"operator":{"min_version":null,"min_operator":null,"max_version":"1.5.7","max_operator":"lt","unfixed":"0","closed":"0"},"source":[{"id":"CVE-2021-24261","name":"CVE-2021-24261","link":"https:\/\/www.cve.org\/CVERecord?id=CVE-2021-24261","description":"[en] The \u201cHT Mega \u2013 Absolute Addons for Elementor Page Builder\u201d WordPress Plugin before 1.5.7 has several widgets that are vulnerable to stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) by lower-privileged users such as contributors, all via a similar method.","date":"2021-05-05"},{"id":"317941c5f20f8b451814786abd161e68a0eb14fc","name":"WordPress HT Mega plugin <= 1.5.5 - Multiple Authenticated Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities","link":"https:\/\/patchstack.com\/database\/wordpress\/plugin\/ht-mega-for-elementor\/vulnerability\/wordpress-ht-mega-plugin-1-5-5-multiple-authenticated-stored-cross-site-scripting-xss-vulnerabilities","description":"Multiple Authenticated Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities discovered by WordFence in WordPress HT Mega plugin (versions <= 1.5.5).","date":"2021-04-13"},{"id":"d08e035a4e328b2c283f1bc9012f2f10ff907421","name":"HT Mega - Absolute Addons for Elementor Page Builder <= 1.5.5 - Contributor+ Stored Cross-Site Scripting","link":"https:\/\/www.wordfence.com\/threat-intel\/vulnerabilities\/wordpress-plugins\/ht-mega-for-elementor\/ht-mega-absolute-addons-for-elementor-page-builder-155-contributor-stored-cross-site-scripting","description":"The \u201cHT Mega \u2013 Absolute Addons for Elementor Page Builder\u201d WordPress Plugin before 1.5.7 has several widgets that are vulnerable to stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) by lower-privileged users such as contributors, all via a similar method.","date":"2021-04-13"},{"id":"0377705d-29e9-47db-a5bb-8acaf311a38f","name":"HT Mega - Absolute Addons for Elementor Page Builder &lt; 1.5.7 - Contributor+ Stored XSS","link":"https:\/\/wpscan.com\/vulnerability\/0377705d-29e9-47db-a5bb-8acaf311a38f","description":"The &ldquo;HT Mega &ndash; Absolute Addons for Elementor Page Builder&rdquo; WordPress Plugin before 1.5.7 has several widgets that are vulnerable to stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) by lower-privileged users such as contributors, all via a similar method.\r\n\r\nThe &ldquo;htmega_call_to_action&rdquo; widget accepts a &ldquo;callto_action_title_tag&rdquo; parameter. Although the element control lists a fixed set of possible html tags, it is possible to send a &lsquo;save_builder&rsquo; request containing JavaScript in the &ldquo;callto_action_title_tag&rdquo; parameter, which is not filtered and is output without escaping. This JavaScript will then be executed when the saved page is viewed or previewed.\r\n\r\nThe &ldquo;htmega_section_title&rdquo; widget accepts a &ldquo;section_title_tag&rdquo; and a &ldquo;section_subtitle_tag&rdquo; parameter. Although the element control lists a fixed set of possible html tags, it is possible to send a &lsquo;save_builder&rsquo; request containing JavaScript in these parameters, which is not filtered and is output without escaping. This JavaScript will then be executed when the saved page is viewed or previewed.\r\n\r\nThe &ldquo;htmega_accordion&rdquo; widget accepts a &ldquo;accourdion_title_html_tag&rdquo; parameter. Although the element control lists a fixed set of possible html tags, it is possible to send a &lsquo;save_builder&rsquo; request containing JavaScript in the &ldquo;accourdion_title_html_tag&rdquo; parameter, which is not filtered and is output without escaping. This JavaScript will then be executed when the saved page is viewed or previewed.\r\n\r\nAdditionally the following appear to have similar vulnerabilities:\r\nbl_page_title: title_html_tag parameter\r\nbl_post_archive_title: title_html_tag parameter\r\nbl_post_title: blog_title_html_tag parameter \r\nbl_post_author_info: name_html_tag parameter\r\nbl_site_title: title_html_tag parameter\r\n\r\nThese vulnerabilities are nearly identical to the vulnerabilities we have recently disclosed in the main Elementor plugin: https:\/\/www.wordfence.com\/blog\/2021\/03\/cross-site-scripting-vulnerabilities-in-elementor-impact-over-7-million-sites\/","date":null}],"impact":{"cvss":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:L\/PR:L\/UI:R\/S:C\/C:L\/I:L\/A:N","av":"n","ac":"l","pr":"l","ui":"r","s":"c","c":"l","i":"l","a":"n","score":"5.4","severity":"m","exploitable":"2.3","impact":"2.7"},"cvss3":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:L\/PR:L\/UI:R\/S:C\/C:L\/I:L\/A:N","score":"5.4","severity":"medium","av":"network","ac":"low","pr":"low","ui":"required","s":"changed","c":"low","i":"low","a":"none","exploitable":"2.3","impact":"2.7"},"cwe":[{"cwe":"CWE-79","name":"Improper Neutralization of Input During Web Page Generation ('Cross-site Scripting')","description":"The product does not neutralize or incorrectly neutralizes user-controllable input before it is placed in output that is used as a web page that is served to other users."}]}},{"uuid":"524cb01d8da8894ba9a1fb69d15327e698c2cf690da4845ff452570bf4741500","name":"HT Mega Addons for Elementor &#8211; Elementor Widgets &amp; Template Builder [ht-mega-for-elementor] < 1.7.0","description":null,"operator":{"min_version":null,"min_operator":null,"max_version":"1.7.0","max_operator":"lt","unfixed":"0","closed":"0"},"source":[{"id":"9da0e2801fa5a0cc61f9067520f3c9c75261da3d","name":"WordPress HT Mega plugin <= 1.6.9 - SQL injection (SQLi) vulnerability","link":"https:\/\/patchstack.com\/database\/wordpr